Officer - IT - PT Leighton Contractors Indonesia
Officer - IT  -
Officer - IT
Responsibilities
To administer the Company information technology systems with the objective of ensuring uninterrupted access to and security of company information. Responsibilities: To administer and maintain company IT systems and infrastructure including hardware and software requirement in order to facilitate efficient information sharing and storage.To facilitate end-user support (queries and concerns) in order to increase productivity of end-users.To maintain and update internal security features in the IT system in order to maintain integrity of company sensitive information.To maintain a register of all computer and information management system equipment including software in order to ensure compliance with license agreements and internal company procedures.To administer and maintain company IT system and equipment including photocopies, printers, faxes in order to ensure high efficiency of equipment.To enforce safe and environmentally friendly working procedures in order to ensure the excellent safety record and encourage employee participation in health and safety matters in order to comply with statutory requirements and HSE expectation. Requirements: Diploma in an IT related field1 - 2 years experienceRelevant document control experience in software and hardware setup administration is preferred.Have an exposure of IT procedures.Experience working at mining/civil contractor is preferred For more details and vacancies, please click on the link below:http://www.leightonasia.com/en/our-people/Pages/job-search.aspx or by clicking the link below:http://www.leightonasia.com/en/our-people/Pages/current-openings.aspx
